TITLE: Generating Base64 Placeholder from Local Image with Node.js
DESCRIPTION: Example of converting a local image file into a low-resolution base64-encoded image placeholder using plaiceholder in Node.js.
SOURCE: https://github.com/joe-bell/plaiceholder/blob/main/docs/pages/docs/usage.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import fs from "node:fs/promises";
import { getPlaiceholder } from "plaiceholder";

try {
  const file = await fs.readFile("/path-to-your-image.jpg");

  const { base64 } = await getPlaiceholder(file);

  console.log(base64);
} catch (err) {
  err;
}

// Logs
// data:image/jpeg;base64,/9j/2wBDAAYEBQY…
```

