TITLE: Implementing Remote Image Resolver with Node.js for Plaiceholder 3.0
DESCRIPTION: Example code showing how to implement a custom image resolver for remote images. This demonstrates fetching an image and converting it to a buffer before passing it to getPlaiceholder.
SOURCE: https://github.com/joe-bell/plaiceholder/blob/main/docs/pages/docs/upgrading-to-3.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const getImage = async (src: string) => {
  const buffer = await fetch(src).then(async (res) =>
    Buffer.from(await res.arrayBuffer())
  );

  const {
    metadata: { height, width },
    ...plaiceholder
  } = await getPlaiceholder(buffer, { size: 10 });

  return {
    ...plaiceholder,
    img: { src, height, width },
  };
};

// Usage
